CR27 PANEL LAYOUT TOOL
PROJECT ANCHORS — DO NOT BREAK THESE

-------------------------------------
CORE PHILOSOPHY
-------------------------------------
This is a FIELD TOOL, not a toy.

The purpose of this system is:
- prevent bad panel cuts
- visualize layout clearly
- reflect real-world install logic

If a change does not improve clarity or reliability → DO NOT ADD IT


-------------------------------------
LAYOUT RULES (LAW)
-------------------------------------
1. Panels ALWAYS start at 0 (left origin)
2. Panel coverage is fixed (default 36")
3. Ribs are spaced at 12" on center
4. Layout is PANEL-DRIVEN, not opening-driven

Openings DO NOT:
- shift layout
- redefine panel positions

Openings ONLY:
- generate cuts
- generate warnings

Violation of this = system failure


-------------------------------------
RIB LOGIC (CRITICAL)
-------------------------------------
Rib centers per panel:
S (Seam) = 0"
R2 = 12"
R3 = 24"
O (Overlap) = 36"

WARNING CONDITION:
If opening edge is within ±0.5" of rib center → FLAG

Ribs intersecting inside opening = OK
Rib landing on jamb edge = NOT OK


-------------------------------------
SIDEWALL MODEL
-------------------------------------
- Horizontal layout defines panels
- Wall Height applies vertically to ALL panels
- Panels run full height unless cut by opening

WallHeight is REQUIRED for:
- cut sheets
- real-world panel length output

WallHeight does NOT affect horizontal layout


-------------------------------------
GABLE MODEL
-------------------------------------
- Height varies across X
- Panels defined by same horizontal system
- Heights interpolated from:
  - left eave
  - ridge
  - right eave

Ridge:
- must be visually clear
- must not conflict with dimension labels

Gable logic must remain linear interpolation
No curve logic. No fancy nonsense.


-------------------------------------
OPENINGS SYSTEM
-------------------------------------
Openings are overlays, not drivers.

Each opening has:
- start (X)
- width

Future:
- sill height
- head height

Openings generate:
- panel cut segments
- warning checks

They do NOT:
- modify panel layout
- snap panels


-------------------------------------
SUMMARY RULES
-------------------------------------
Summary must remain:
- short
- readable
- field-relevant

Sidewall summary includes:
- Wall Length
- Wall Height
- Panel Coverage
- Full Panels
- Non-standard panels ONLY

Do NOT list every panel unless necessary


-------------------------------------
SVG RENDER RULES
-------------------------------------
The drawing is the PRIMARY OUTPUT

Must always show:
- wall boundary
- panel seams
- ribs
- openings
- dimensions

Rules:
- readable > detailed
- avoid label clutter
- ridge must stand out
- spacing must prevent overlap

If it looks confusing → it is wrong


-------------------------------------
UI RULES
-------------------------------------
- Inputs grouped logically
- No dead states
- Layout always renders if valid

DO NOT:
- overbuild controls
- add unnecessary toggles
- turn this into CAD software


-------------------------------------
GIT RULES
-------------------------------------
main = FIELD SAFE
experimental = sandbox

NEVER:
- test risky changes on main

ONLY merge to main when:
- tested
- stable
- trusted in field


-------------------------------------
DEPLOYMENT RULES
-------------------------------------
Wasmer / Pages deploy from main ONLY

experimental is NOT public

Live tool must always be:
- stable
- predictable
- usable under pressure


-------------------------------------
DEVELOPMENT RULE
-------------------------------------
Before adding ANY feature:

Ask:
1. Does this prevent mistakes?
2. Does this improve clarity?
3. Would I trust this on a job?

If NO → do not build it


-------------------------------------
FINAL RULE
-------------------------------------
Do not break what works.
Ever.

(Yes, this means you.)